article.description: Mike Morsell sank a pair of free throws with 18 seconds left to build a seven-point cushion and Towson held on to defeat Fairleigh Dickinson 90-87 on Saturday in a game that saw a combined 84 fre
article.headline: Towson holds off Fairleigh Dickinson 90-87 amid 57 fouls
article.linkText: Towson holds off Fairleigh Dickinson 90-87 amid 57 fouls
article.story: TOWSON, Md. -- Mike Morsell sank a pair of free throws with 18 seconds left to build a seven-point cushion and Towson held on to defeat Fairleigh Dickinson 90-87 on Saturday in a game that saw a combined 84 free throws. Morsell and John Davis each scored 18 points to lead Towson (6-4), with Morsell shooting 12-for-16 at the foul line. Arnaud Adala Moto was 8-for-10 at the line and scored 14 points as the Tigers took advantage of 32 fouls to score 36 points on free throws. Darian Anderson, who poured in a career-best 33 points, scored twice in the final 13 seconds to pull Fairleigh Dickinson (2-7) within three. Anderson made six 3-pointers. Stephan Jiggetts scored a season-high 25 points for the Knights and Earl Potts, Jr. added 13. Fairleigh Dickinson converted 21 of 31 foul shots on 25 Towson fouls.
